8 Subject: Fish and wildlife; furbearers; use of bait
9 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to prohibit a
10 person from taking a furbearer by gun, bow and arrow, or crossbow with the
11 use of bait.
12 An act relating to the taking of furbearers
13 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
14 Sec. 1. 10 V.S.A. § 4866 is added to read:
15 § 4866. TAKING OF FURBEARERS; USE OF BAIT
16 (a) As used in this section, “bait” means any animal, vegetable, fruit, or
17 mineral matter placed with the intention of attracting wildlife. “Bait” does not
18 mean animal, vegetable, or fruit matter placed by a person subject to the
19 Required Agricultural Practices as part of standard agricultural production.
